From 47427b95c7339fcaff2f6fa21a190b078010395f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kas User <kas@example.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 11:58:49 +0530
Subject: initramfs-framework: limit udev trigger to block devices only

Add patch to restrict udevadm trigger to block devices during initramfs
boot by adding '--subsystem-match=block' to the udevadm trigger command.

Without this filter, udevadm trigger fires for all subsystems (net,
input, usb, etc.) during early boot, causing unnecessary delays while
waiting for non-critical devices to settle. Limiting to block devices
ensures only storage devices are enumerated in the initramfs stage,
reducing boot latency.

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: Kas User <kas@example.com>
---
 udev | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/udev b/udev
index 4898b89246..3a9af2dc38 100644
--- a/udev
+++ b/udev
@@ -45,6 +45,6 @@ udev_run() {
 	sh -c "exec 4< /dev/console" || { exec 0> /dev/null; exec 1> /dev/null; exec 2> /dev/null; }
 
 	$_UDEV_DAEMON --daemon
-	udevadm trigger --action=add
+	udevadm trigger --subsystem-match=block --action=add
 	udevadm settle
 }
